Messenger App
=============

Messaging application with private and group chats, real-time message delivery,
presence tracking, and avatar support.
Built as a modular, service-oriented Flask application.

Tech Stack
----------

Backend:  Flask, Flask-SocketIO, Flask-Login, Flask-WTF, SQLAlchemy, Marshmallow
Database: SQLite (development), PostgreSQL (production)
Cache & real-time: Redis (session store, rate limiting, presence, message queue)
Frontend: TypeScript compiled via Webpack, served as static files

Getting Started
---------------

Prerequisites

- Python 3.9+
- Node.js 18+ and npm (for frontend build)
- Redis server running locally (or via Docker)

Installation

1. Clone the repository
   git clone https://github.com/user1149/messanger.git
   cd messanger

2. Create and activate a virtual environment
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate

3. Install Python dependencies
   pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Configure environment variables
   cp .env.example .env
   Edit .env if needed (see Configuration below).

5. Build the frontend
   cd frontend
   npm install
   npm run build
   cd ..

6. Start Redis server (if not already running)
   - Using Docker:
     docker run --name redis -p 6379:6379 -d redis
   - Using local installation:
     redis-server

7. Run the application
   python run.py

   Optional flags:
     --debug          Enable debug mode
     --host 0.0.0.0   Bind to all interfaces (default: 127.0.0.1)
     --port 8080       Custom port (default: 5000)
     --unsafe          Allow Werkzeug reloader in production

The app will be available at http://localhost:5000.

Configuration
-------------

Key environment variables (see .env.example for all options):

FLASK_ENV          - development, production, or testing (default: development)
SECRET_KEY         - secret key for sessions (change in production!)
DATABASE_URL       - database connection string (default: sqlite:///instance/messenger.db)
REDIS_URL          - Redis connection string (default: redis://localhost:6379/0)
REDIS_URL_TEST     - Redis DB for tests (default: redis://localhost:6379/15)
BASE_URL           - base URL of the application (default: http://localhost:5000)
CORS_ORIGINS       - comma-separated allowed origins (default: http://localhost:3000)
SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE - set to False in development (default: True)

Rate limits (requests per second, configured in code):

new_message        - 4 per second
create_private_chat - 1 per second
join_chat          - 3 per second
typing             - 2 per second
mark_read          - 5 per second
login attempts     - 10 per 15 minutes per IP

Project Structure
-----------------

project/
  run.py                        Entry point; parses CLI args, checks Redis, starts server
  requirements.txt              Python dependencies

  app/
    __init__.py                 Exposes create_app()
    core/
      config.py                 DevelopmentConfig / TestingConfig / ProductionConfig
      extensions.py             Shared Flask extensions (db, login_manager, csrf, socketio)
      factory.py                Application factory; wires extensions, blueprints, error handlers
      di.py                     Dependency injection container (Container class)
      logging.py                Structured audit logging helpers
      base/
        repository.py           Base repository with common DB helpers
        schema.py               Base Marshmallow schema
      exceptions/
        base.py                 Base application exception
        auth_errors.py          Auth-related exceptions (InvalidCredentials, RateLimit, etc.)
        chat_errors.py          Chat-related exceptions (AccessDenied, MessageNotFound, etc.)
      utils/
        constants.py            Enums / constants (ChatType, ValidationRules, SocketEvent, etc.)
        decorators.py           @handle_errors and @socket_authenticated decorators
        rate_limit.py           Redis-backed per-user rate limiting for Socket.IO actions
        validators.py           Input validation helpers (username, message text, file ext.)
        helpers.py              Miscellaneous utility functions

    models/
      user.py                   User (id, username, password_hash, bio, avatar_url)
      chat.py                   Chat (id, name, type: private|group, created_by, description)
      chat_participant.py       ChatParticipant join table
      private_chat.py           PrivateChat helper model
      message.py                Message (id, chat_id, user_id, text, timestamp, edited, is_deleted)
      last_read.py              LastRead (user_id, chat_id, last_message_id)

    modules/
      auth/
        routes.py               POST /auth/login, POST /auth/register, POST /auth/logout
                                GET  /api/auth/me
        services.py             AuthService: register, login, rate-limited by IP
        schemas.py              UserLoginSchema, UserRegisterSchema (Marshmallow)

      users/
        routes.py               GET  /api/users?q=   (search, min 2 chars)
                                GET  /api/users/<id>
                                GET  /api/users/by-username/<username>
                                GET  /api/profile
                                PUT  /api/profile
                                POST /api/profile/avatar  (upload PNG/JPG/GIF, max 10 MB)
        services.py             UserService, ProfileService
        repositories.py         UserRepository

      chats/
        services.py             ChatService: get_user_chats, get_unread_counts
        repositories.py         ChatRepository: private/group chat CRUD, participants

      groups/
        services.py             GroupService: create_group, create_private_chat,
                                add/remove members, get_group_info

      messages/
        services.py             MessageService: send, history, mark_read,
                                edit (5 min window), delete (5 min window)
        repositories/           MessageRepository, LastReadRepository

      presence/
        services.py             PresenceService: track online/offline via Redis TTL keys

      pages/
        routes.py               Serves index.html and auth.html templates

    socket/
      handlers.py               Registers Socket.IO namespaces
      namespaces.py
        ChatNamespace    /chat      join_chat, new_message, typing, mark_read,
                                   edit_message, delete_message,
                                   create_private_chat, get_chat_list
        PresenceNamespace /presence connect / disconnect hooks
        GroupNamespace   /groups   create_group, get_group_info,
                                   add_to_group, remove_from_group, leave_group

  templates/
    auth.html                   Login / registration page
    index.html                  Main chat UI
    modals/                     Modal dialog partials

  static/
    css/                        Compiled styles
    js/                         Compiled TypeScript bundles

  frontend/
    src/
      main.ts                   App bootstrap
      auth.ts                   Login / register logic
      chat.ts                   Chat list and message rendering
      socket.ts                 Socket.IO client wrapper
      ui.ts                     DOM helpers and UI state
      profile.ts                Profile and avatar upload
      utils.ts                  Shared utilities
      types/                    TypeScript type definitions
      styles/                   SCSS source files
    webpack.config.js           Webpack bundler config
    tsconfig.json               TypeScript compiler config
    package.json                npm scripts: build (production), dev (watch)

Features
--------

- Username / password authentication with session cookies
- Per-IP login rate limiting (Redis)
- Private chats (one-to-one, auto-created on first message)
- Group chats with creator-managed membership
- Real-time message delivery via Socket.IO (WebSocket)
- Typing indicators broadcast to chat participants
- Message editing and soft-deletion within a 5-minute window
- Unread message counters per chat
- User presence (online / offline) tracked via Redis TTL
- User search by username prefix
- Avatar upload (PNG, JPG, GIF; max 10 MB)
- User bio / profile page
- CSRF protection on all state-changing HTTP routes
- Structured audit logging (login, registration, message edits/deletions)
- Custom JSON error responses for all application exceptions
- DI container for clean dependency management across services

Running Tests
-------------

pytest
pytest --cov=app

Tests use an in-memory SQLite database and Redis DB 15 (configurable via REDIS_URL_TEST).
CSRF is disabled automatically in the testing configuration.

Production Deployment
---------------------

1. Set FLASK_ENV=production in your environment.
2. Use a real SECRET_KEY (long random string).
3. Set DATABASE_URL to your PostgreSQL connection string.
4. Set SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=True (already the default in production).
5. Run with Gunicorn + eventlet or gevent for async Socket.IO support:
   gunicorn -k eventlet -w 1 "app:create_app()"

